OL,3,CRow over proposed 8.5% council tax
OL,4,Crise in Scottish Borders
OL,6,FNow, along with the Scottish Greens,
OL,7,Fthey have proposed their own amendment
OL,8,Finstead.
OL,10,FThe administration draft budget
OL,11,Fpresented an 8.5% rise in council tax
OL,12,Ffor 2026/27 but boasted of protecting
OL,13,Fservices from cuts including bus
OL,14,Fservices, road infrastructure,
OL,15,Finvesting #33m into developing care
OL,16,Fvillages, and spending on new school
OL,17,Fbuildings like Peebles High,
OL,18,FGalashiels Academy, and Earlston
OL,19,FPrimary, with Hawick high school under
OL,20,Fconstruction.
