OL,3,CRow over proposed 8.5% council tax
OL,4,Crise in Scottish Borders
OL,6,FThe point of contention was over the
OL,7,Fcouncil tax rate of 8.5% for average
OL,8,Fhouseholds, but also the proposed
OL,9,Fphased introduction of a higher rate
OL,10,Fof council tax for second homes.
OL,12,FSNP and Greens will share an amendment
OL,13,Fahead of the Scottish Borders Council
OL,14,Fmeeting on Thursday 19th February.
OL,16,FWhile figures for the amendment are
OL,17,Fstill being considered it proposes an
OL,18,Fimmediate introduction of higher
OL,19,Fcouncil tax for second homes, and a
OL,20,Fcouncil tax figure of the average
OL,21,Fhousehold to be closer to 8%.
