OL,3,CRow over proposed 8.5% council tax
OL,4,Crise in Scottish Borders
OL,6,F"Our priority is to protect local
OL,7,Fresidents and ensure fairness in how
OL,8,Fcouncil tax is applied. Those who
OL,9,Fchoose to own second or long-term
OL,10,Fempty homes should contribute more to
OL,11,Fthe communities that sustain those
OL,12,Fproperties.
OL,14,F"At the same time, we recognise that
OL,15,Fcommunities need practical support,
OL,16,Fwhether that is taking on local assets
OL,17,Ffollowing the Live Borders review, or
OL,18,Fensuring that energy applications are
OL,19,Fproperly scrutinised and managed. Our
OL,20,Famendment reflects those priorities."
